metadata.description:

metadata.name: the boxes we live in #269
metadata.description:
Throughout our lives we are placed in boxes that define who we are and limit how we think of ourselves. 

I am a father, husband, son, brother, friend. I am an artist, programmer, photographer, musician, designer, creator. I am a student and I am a teacher. I am a good person. I am a bad person. I am a human.

What boxes do you put yourself in, and do you let others put you in? Is it possible to break out of the boxes that define your life? Do you even want to? What's outside of these boundaries? What is at the center?

metadata.name: Concrete #355
metadata.description:
640 unique sketches of imaginary walls, inspired by the work of Norwegian architect Erling Viksjø (1910–1971) and his artist collaborators. Viksjø designed the Government Quarter in Oslo and invited artists from different disciplines to help design the facades and interiors of the buildings.

Viksjø’s aim was to “soften” modernist architecture. He invented «Natural Concrete», a type of concrete that deliberately exposes the mixed-in stones on its surface to give it warmth and a human touch. In my work, I have similar ambitions—using code instead of concrete.

The different styles of the piece are inspired by, and dedicated to some of the artists who worked together with Viksjø: Jakob Weidemann (~2%), Carl Nesjar (~18%), Odd Tandberg (~30%), and Tore Haaland (~50%).

In live mode, press ‘S’ to save an image at current resolution or ‘P’ to save a high-resolution file at 6000×6000px (this might take a while depending on your hardware).

Original artwork by Andreas Rau · Made with p5.js & glsl · Oslo, 2021

metadata.name: Dancing Line 燕舞 #176
metadata.description:
This work is inspired by thinking about lines. Points, lines, and surfaces are the most basic elements of art. Whether or not an art work can be made using only lines and colors is a direction that has been explored recently. By connecting points at different distances, the color and transparency can produce different light and shade effects with the change of distance. In addition, a rotation algorithm is generated during the connection process, which can create light and shade, density, and the beauty of curves with relatively rich layers. , like a swallow dancing in the air is the resulting arc path. Hence the name Yanwu. Of course, another Chinese meaning of Yanwu is a brand of early Chinese TV sets, which also commemorates the era of creativity. I am also grateful to be able to contribute to the construction of Web3. There are 3 background colors, 7 line colors, and 30 dance times in this work, among which there are millions of combinations of point positions. This work only displays the background color, line color and dance times in the feature information.
Made With P5.js.
20% of royalties will be donated to the Processing Foundation.

The following is the description in Chinese.
作品燕舞：
当足够的线条沿着特殊的轨迹进行排列，
并且线条的数量足够多的时候，
就会让画面给人以美感的同时，
产生足够震撼的力量。
燕舞因为生成过程有曲线路径，
像燕子在空中飞舞留下的痕迹。
当然燕舞的另外一个中文意思一个早期中国电视机的一个品牌，
也以此纪念那个创意勃发的年代。也同时希望能够为Web3贡献一份力量。
此作品共有3中背景色彩，7中线条色彩，以及30种舞动次数随机组合，
其中点的位置有百万种组合，此作品只把背景色，
线条颜色和舞动次数作品特色点显示在作品信息中，
此作品基于p5js语言完成

metadata.name: Nounfall #32
metadata.description:
Nounfall is drawn exclusively from the 234 heads and 21 glasses that are used to build the current Nouns collection. The background colors are all pulled from the blessed Noun palette.

This is ok because Nouns are CC0, which basically means public domain. Check out nouns.wtf for more info.

They make for fun social media banners when cropped, if you wanna show off you fandom of Nouns.

C : Clear screen and start animation over
S : Save current image
1 -> 6 : Set pixel density to the respective number

So, if you want a high resolution file, tap `6` for it to redraw, and then `S` to save. You can also save while it's animating if you like, which is fun too.

metadata.name: FairyCells II #175
metadata.description:
FairyCells II is intended as a logical continuation of the first FairyCells series. By dropping the plotter drawing constraint, new perspectives for exploration appeared.
This is how these cells began to intertwine, live together, mutate and change color, like an evolving system.

What surprises me the most in this new series, is the stories appearing behind each new composition. See how these abstracts shapes can come to life and narrate us things through our imagination.

Each color palette takes us into a different world, drawing a very specific atmosphere.

As me, let yourself be carried away by these stories 💫 !

Artwork by Julien_Espagnon, 2022.

Control : Press « S » to save the image as a PNG.

metadata.name: Elevation #189
metadata.description:
There’s so much more to our world than what we are able to perceive, let alone understand. Will we ever be able to even fully understand ourselves?

–

Elevation is a series of 320 generative elevation drawings of imaginary structures. It is a reminder of the limits of our consciousness, and an ode to the manifold nuances that lie beyond what we can perceive, beyond what we even can imagine.

As a generative artist, I aim to elevate my own consciousness with the help of the machine. I welcome algorithms and randomness into the creation of my works, taking full control, and intentionally giving it away, always seeking to expand my imagination. For as humans alone, we remain limited to our own edifice of thought, and often fail to free ourselves from the visible, mundane world.

Both are present in Elevation: the visible and the imaginary, the mundane and the transcendent, the solid and the fragile. Where an architect’s elevation drawing marks the transition from the thought world into the visible world, Elevation remains in-between, depicting both the idea of an imaginary structure, and the structure itself.

–

Elevation is intended for print. All holders of an Elevation NFT will be able to order the corresponding signed print in the respective paper format via andreasrau.eu/elevation. Press [s] to save the image as displayed or [p] to generate a print-ready PNG image at 300 dpi. This might take a while, depending on paper format and your hardware.

–

metadata.name: Sketch B #8
metadata.description:
Sketch is an open-ended series. Works evolve as I code a generative project, sometimes drastically. Intermediate works usually don't see the light of day - they get archived and forgotten. This series is snapshots of different forms along the way - each standing alone, but also part of a larger meandering work flow. The word Sketch implies incompleteness. This project may end up being two works, or it could evolve for years. Part of the joy of generative art is never knowing what's around the corner. I have no set schedule. There may be multiple Sketches released a week, or it could be weeks or months between drops. I have no idea where Sketch is heading and there is no guarantee of cohesiveness from Sketch to Sketch. Color palettes and forms will change as new ideas are explored.

Sketch B remains simple. The basic grid of Sketch A is there, but is starting to be filled. Grid lines are trimmed as if sketched. Colors continue to be borrowed from Echos/Orbits and new colors from Bent are incorporated. Grid size, padding, line thickness, fill color, and fill percentage and patterns vary.

metadata.name: Rain Ritual #155
metadata.description:
Every windy gust.... every breeze, gave the restless grasses a chance to spread their suggestive rumours, their spurious gossip. All the while, Old Ones of the field towered above, chanting to their wrathful Sky God for more rain.... Always more rain. 

Instructions 
Intended for high resolutions. Use the following keys once render is complete, to export (letters export without a border) 

Square mode 
   1 (q) : 2048x2048  
   2 (w) : 3072x3072 
   3 (e) : 4096x4096 
   4 (r) : 5120x5120 

Landscape mode (increases spacing between objects to preserve aspect ratio) 
   5 (t) : 2560x1440 
   6 (y) : 3840x2160 
   7 (u) : 5128x2880 
   8 (I) : 7680x4320 

Note: Generated textures are resolution dependant, resulting in very slight differences across resolutions. Composition however, remains identical. 

Browsers 
Tested with Chrome, Edge and Firefox on Windows, Chrome on Mac. 
Note for Firefox users : Ensure "Use hardware acceleration" is ticked – Found in Settings / Performance. Other advanced settings to enable include : gfx.canvas.accelerated,  gfx.direct2d.force-enabled and gfx.offscreencanvas.enabled - Unfortunately even with these, Firefox appears slower than other browsers.
